I'd solve it the other way around myself. Give all spells a mininum level they will 'stick' on, make the default zero. If you aren't that level it doesn't stick on you. Solves a few problems, some classes get spells other classes get at a much later level. This would let them cast those spells on the same range of people after they get them. And it lets them tailor the levels to fit better with what the spells are. And instead of checking the target, the recipient does the checking so it would work even with MGB. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
